  "texts": [
    "There are also several societal consequences that are derived from such an enormous outbreak of LLMs which are specialized to do specific human tasks, and thus potentially depriving humans of their professions.",
    "Nevertheless, it must be made clear that the machines themselves will not be able to replace human jobs, because they lack agency as we showed earlier.",
    "The agency comes only from humans, so it will be humans who are using the machines that will replace other humans who do not know how to use them.",
    "We are heading into a new form of society of AI-knowledgeable \"experts\" and AI-illiterate ones.",
    "This potential separatism that, in part, is already happening as we speak, gave birth into a new field of science that is called \"AI-Ethics\".Even though terminologically \"AI-Ethics\" presents a schema oxymoron, since all the current models lack Agency, this field must be accounted for as a very important part of the current evolutionary step of our society."
  ],
